column1: Before you can fire an event, you need to register it. The recommended way to do that is in the constructor of your class because this constructor is guaranteed to be called before whatever code. What happens behind the scenes is pretty simple: The event you are registering is placed into a dictionary held by the `EventProviderHelper` instance of your class. This dictionary is used later when firing events and for the `GetRegisteredEvents()` implementation.","- sldkjfsldfj
